Seamless Bay Area is proud to be part of a broad coalition of Bay Area transit advocates and planners supporting AB 629.

We're deeply grateful to Asm. @DavidChiu for his commitment to creating a more connected and rider-friendly transit network in our region.
This bill builds on the momentum created by Asm. Chiu's AB 2057 last year, as well as the work of the Bay Area Blue Ribbon Transit Recovery Task Force.

AB 269 also directs MTC to work with transit agencies to identify and maintain a coordinated transit priority network for the region, which would keep transit riders moving quickly across transit agency boundaries.
This bill prioritizes the rider experience by directing Bay Area transit agencies to work together on coordinated transit fares, signage and wayfinding, and real time arrival information. üöè
